metadata.description: With over 15 years of experience, Bibek specializes in cultural tours of the Kathmandu Valley. He has deep knowledge of Newari architecture, Hindu and Buddhist traditions, and can provide insights into local festivals and customs. Fluent in multiple languages, he makes complex cultural concepts accessible to all visitors.

metadata.description: A certified mountain guide from the Solu Khumbu region, Keshab has led over 200 treks including Everest Base Camp, Annapurna Circuit, and Langtang. He is passionate about photography and knows the best spots for capturing the Himalayas. His Sherpa heritage gives him unique insights into mountain culture.

metadata.description: Sushant is a cultural expert specializing in Buddhist philosophy and meditation practices. He leads tours to Lumbini, the birthplace of Buddha, and various meditation centers. His gentle approach and deep understanding of spiritual traditions make his tours transformative experiences.

metadata.description: A wildlife enthusiast and photographer, Subodh specializes in Chitwan and Bardia National Parks. He has extensive knowledge of Nepal flora and fauna, including rare bird species and the one-horned rhinoceros. His Tharu heritage provides authentic insights into Terai culture.

metadata.description: Born and raised in Patan, Sushant is a Newari culture expert who offers immersive food tours and cultural experiences. He can take you to hidden local eateries, explain Newari traditions, and show you the intricate details of Newari architecture. His tours are like visiting a friend home.
